Estimating mRNA secondary structure stability at 30C with ensemble deltaG, minimum free energy (mfe) deltaG, and mean base-pair probability

3/15/2023

library(car)
library(lme4)
library(reshape2)

Figure 2B - analysis of mF on full set of genes

DeltaG of the minimum free energy (mfe) structure

Menu
Define the response variable, logPPR.
response <- read.csv('n_PPR_1458_d.csv')
dataset <- melt(response, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "PPR")
dataset$logPPR <- log(dataset$PPR)
Read in Data
explanatory0 <- read.csv('optimal_struc_mfe_1458_30C.csv')
explanatory0 <- melt(explanatory0, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "optimalG")
dataset$optimalG <- explanatory0$optimalG/10000 #divide resulting slope by 10 to get to Mcal/mol
Summary Results of Mixed Model
lmm1 <- lmer(logPPR ~ optimalG + (1+optimalG|gene), data=dataset, REML = FALSE, control = lmerControl(optimizer="bobyqa", optCtrl=list(maxfun=1e5)))
summary(lmm1)
## Linear mixed model fit by maximum likelihood  ['lmerMod']
## Formula: logPPR ~ optimalG + (1 + optimalG | gene)
##    Data: dataset
## Control: lmerControl(optimizer = "bobyqa", optCtrl = list(maxfun = 1e+05))
## 
##      AIC      BIC   logLik deviance df.resid 
## -99482.7 -99432.4  49747.3 -99494.7    32070 
## 
## Scaled residuals: 
##      Min       1Q   Median       3Q      Max 
## -15.0922  -0.4185   0.0285   0.4559  11.7956 
## 
## Random effects:
##  Groups   Name        Variance  Std.Dev. Corr
##  gene     (Intercept)  0.734326 0.85693      
##           optimalG    72.061792 8.48892  0.26
##  Residual              0.001729 0.04158      
## Number of obs: 32076, groups:  gene, 1458
## 
## Fixed effects:
##             Estimate Std. Error t value
## (Intercept)   7.5392     0.0362 208.257
## optimalG     -4.4201     0.6501  -6.799
## 
## Correlation of Fixed Effects:
##          (Intr)
## optimalG 0.778
95% Confidence Interval of Mixed Model
confint(lmm1, parm="optimalG", level=0.95)
## Computing profile confidence intervals ...
##              2.5 %    97.5 %
## optimalG -5.724468 -3.129687
Fixed Effects Slope Significance Results
lmm01 <- lmer(logPPR ~ (1+optimalG|gene), data=dataset, REML = FALSE, control = lmerControl(optimizer="Nelder_Mead", optCtrl=list(maxfun=1e5)))
anova(lmm1, lmm01)
## Data: dataset
## Models:
## lmm01: logPPR ~ (1 + optimalG | gene)
## lmm1: logPPR ~ optimalG + (1 + optimalG | gene)
##       npar    AIC    BIC logLik deviance  Chisq Df Pr(>Chisq)    
## lmm01    5 -99440 -99398  49725   -99450                         
## lmm1     6 -99483 -99432  49747   -99495 44.507  1  2.534e-11 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
Diagnostic Plots
par(mfrow=c(2,2))
res = residuals(lmm1)

scatter.smooth(fitted(lmm1), res, col='cornflowerblue', span=0.1, xlab='Fitted Values', ylab='Residuals')
scatter.smooth(dataset$optimal, res, col='cornflowerblue', span=0.1, xlab="mfe DeltaG Scaled by 1/10000", ylab='Residuals')
qqnorm(res, col='cornflowerblue')
qqline(res)
hist(res, main='', xlab='Residuals', ylab='Frequency', col='cornflowerblue')

rm(list = ls(all.names = TRUE))

Arithmetic mean gene basepair probability

Menu
Define the response variable, logPPR.
response <- read.csv('n_PPR_1458_d.csv')
dataset <- melt(response, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "PPR")
dataset$logPPR <- log(dataset$PPR)
Read in Data
explanatory0 <- read.csv('mean_gene_bp_prob_1458_30C.csv')
explanatory0 <- melt(explanatory0, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "bp_prob")
dataset$bp_prob <- explanatory0$bp_prob
Summary Results of Mixed Model
lmm2 <- lmer(logPPR ~ bp_prob + (1+bp_prob|gene), data=dataset, REML = FALSE, control = lmerControl(optimizer="bobyqa", optCtrl=list(maxfun=1e5)))

Define the response variable, logPPR.
response <- read.csv("n_PPR_1458_d.csv")
dataset <- melt(response, id.vars = "gene", variable.name = "strain", value.name = "PPR")
dataset$logPPR <- log(dataset$PPR)
Read in Data
explanatory0 <- read.csv('ensemble_fe_1458_30C.csv')

dataset$ensembleG = explanatory0$ensembleG/10000 #divide resulting slope by 10 to get to Mcal/mol

#include median protein abundance for each gene

explanatory1 <- read.csv('PA_medians_1458.csv')

dataset$medianPA = explanatory1$medianPA/10000

Diagnostic Plots
par(mfrow=c(2,2))
res = residuals(lmm0)

scatter.smooth(fitted(lmm0), res, col='cornflowerblue', span=0.1, xlab='Fitted Values', ylab='Residuals')
scatter.smooth(dataset$ensembleG, res, col='cornflowerblue', span=0.1, xlab="Ensemble DeltaG Scaled by 1/10000", ylab='Residuals')
qqnorm(res, col='cornflowerblue')
qqline(res)
hist(res, main='', xlab='Residuals', ylab='Frequency', col='cornflowerblue')

rm(list = ls(all.names = TRUE))
